# Commit and push

When the user asks to commit and/or push:

1. Max **29** commits this session. Split real work into small logical commits.
2. No empty or junk commits. Do not change git config.
3. Prefer feature branch + PR (`gh pr create`) when it helps review or Pull Shark.
4. Use `Co-authored-by` only if the project documents a real second GitHub identity.
5. Author email should remain the repo’s configured identity (contribution email on GitHub).
6. Never force-push main/master unless the user explicitly asks.
